Class ServerConstants

      • chooseInterface

        public static java.net.NetworkInterface chooseInterface()
                                                 throws java.net.SocketException
        Chooses running network interface to work with.

        Gets a list of system's running interfaces and tries to get a wired interface first, then if none, attempts to get wireless interface. If none of them were found, returns null.

        Returns:
        running network interface to work with or null if none.
        Throws:
        java.net.SocketException - when can't get an enumeration of interfaces from system.

      • chooseInterface

        private static java.net.NetworkInterface chooseInterface(java.util.ArrayList<java.net.NetworkInterface> nics,
                                                         java.lang.String key)
        Searches for the interface by a keyword in it's name.

        Searches in a list of network interfaces for the first one with the name, containing the key.

        Parameters:
        nics - List of network interfaces;
        key - String key;
        Returns:
        Found interface and null if none.
